        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 3:30PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 329 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Elliston-Lafayette, or near Shawsville, moving
northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Roanoke...
Salem...
Vinton...
Bedford...
Buchanan...
Troutville...
and Stewartsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors,seek shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
